etymologies: mid 17th century: from Turkish paşa, from Pahlavi pati ‘lord’ + šāh ‘shah’

definitions: the title of a Turkish officer of high rank.
shortDefinitions: title of Turkish officer of high rank

definitions: a large orange-brown butterfly with two tails on each hind wing and complex patterns on the underwings, occurring around the Mediterranean and in Africa.

notes.text: Charaxes jasius, subfamily Nymphalinae, family Nymphalidae

shortDefinitions: large orange-brown butterfly with two tails on each hindwing and complex patterns on underwings
